            {"name": "Banu Haqim", "description": "Warrior-scholars and assassins of Middle Eastern origin. The Banu Haqim serve as judges and enforcers in Kindred society, hunting those who break the laws of the night. They are deadly, precise, and deeply moral — at least by their own code.", "bane": "Blood Addiction: When a Banu Haqim feeds on another vampire's Vitae, they must succeed on a Hunger check or become addicted, craving vampiric blood above mortal.", "compulsion": "Judgment: The vampire must act to correct a wrong or punish a transgressor they witness. They cannot ignore injustice.", "disciplines": ["Blood Sorcery", "Celerity", "Obfuscate"]},
            {"name": "Brujah", "description": "Rebels, philosophers, and warriors who have never forgotten their origins as champions of mortal causes. Brujah fight for ideals — freedom, justice, change — and their passion makes them among the most dangerous Kindred in a brawl.", "bane": "Violent Temper: Brujah reduce the difficulty to resist frenzy by 2, but also find it 2 dice harder to resist frenzy when provoked or insulted.", "compulsion": "Rebellion: The vampire must defy or undermine an authority figure, rule, or order that applies to them. They cannot comply with commands without resistance.", "disciplines": ["Celerity", "Potence", "Presence"]},
