            {"name": "Lasombra", "description": "Aristocratic shadows. The Lasombra ruled as priests, nobles, and leaders for millennia, and their mastery of darkness reflects their nature — beautiful, terrifying, and utterly at home in the dark. They recently joined the Camarilla, uneasy allies in an uneasy age.", "bane": "The Darkness Within: Lasombra cast no reflection in mirrors or cameras. Their image cannot be captured by phones or CCTV — a significant problem in the modern surveillance age.", "compulsion": "Ruthlessness: The vampire must succeed or dominate in the current situation by any means. They cannot accept failure, retreat, or second place without spending Willpower.", "disciplines": ["Dominate", "Oblivion", "Potence"]},
            {"name": "Malkavian", "description": "Seers and madmen touched by a clan-wide psychic curse that grants insight and destroys stability in equal measure. Every Malkavian is broken in some unique way — but that brokenness sometimes shows them truths others cannot perceive.", "bane": "Fractured Perspective: Every Malkavian has a derangement or mental flaw that cannot be bought off. The nature and severity varies, but it always affects their behavior and perception.", "compulsion": "Delusion: The vampire becomes convinced of something false and acts on it. They cannot be argued out of it this scene.", "disciplines": ["Auspex", "Dominate", "Obfuscate"]},
            {"name": "Ministry", "description": "Priests of forbidden pleasures and forgotten gods. The Ministry (once called the Followers of Set) spread corruption and temptation, offering mortals and Kindred exactly what they desire — and collecting the debt. They serve a dark god and keep their own counsel.", "bane": "Children of the Night: Sunlight is especially lethal to Ministry vampires — all sunlight damage is Aggravated, and they treat the damage as one level higher than normal.", "compulsion": "Transgression: The vampire must tempt or corrupt someone nearby — offer them something forbidden or encourage them to break a rule, law, or personal code.", "disciplines": ["Blood Sorcery", "Presence", "Protean"]},
            {"name": "Nosferatu", "description": "Hideous, lurking spies and information brokers condemned to monstrous forms. The Nosferatu are the eyes and ears of Kindred society — they know everything, because no one watches the monster in the sewer. Their ugliness cannot be hidden by any mundane means.", "bane": "Repulsive: Nosferatu are grotesque in ways that cannot be concealed without Obfuscate. All Social rolls with mortals who can see them suffer a 2-dice penalty. Presence cannot mask this.", "compulsion": "Cryptophilia: The vampire must collect and hoard a secret before they can act freely. They become obsessed with learning hidden information.", "disciplines": ["Animalism", "Obfuscate", "Potence"]},
            {"name": "Ravnos", "description": "Wandering tricksters and survivors of a near-extinction event, the Ravnos carry trauma in their blood. Masters of illusion, they drift through Kindred society as travelers, gamblers, and con artists, trusting no one and belonging nowhere.", "bane": "Doomed to Wander: Ravnos cannot remain in one location more than a week without suffering psychological distress. They must move on or fight mounting anxiety.", "compulsion": "Tempting Fate: The vampire must engage in a risky, unnecessary action — gambling, a dare, a wager. They suffer 2 dice penalty on all rolls until they take the risk.", "disciplines": ["Animalism", "Obfuscate", "Presence"]},
